00:26:12,380 --> 00:26:15,660
 from on HKU campus a few years ago.

541
00:26:15,660 --> 00:26:18,700
 We were introducing the service aspect

542
00:26:18,700 --> 00:26:20,420
 of the Character Leadership Program.

543
00:26:20,420 --> 00:26:22,740
 So, we're trying to teach, there's about 600 students

544
00:26:22,740 --> 00:26:25,060
 involved in the program now, all four years.

545
00:26:25,060 --> 00:26:27,100
 It's going to a two-year program next year,

546
00:26:27,100 --> 00:26:28,740
 or actually started this year,

547
00:26:28,740 --> 00:26:32,500
 but we're trying to teach them character leadership.

548
00:26:32,500 --> 00:26:34,260
 How do you develop your character?

549
00:26:34,260 --> 00:26:36,460
 One of those ways that we were doing it at the beginning

550
00:26:36,460 --> 00:26:38,900
 was really to have service projects,

551
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:41,460
 because obviously if you're serving someone else,

552
00:26:41,460 --> 00:26:43,020
 then you're building your character.

553
00:26:43,020 --> 00:26:45,060
 And we tell our students, "It's not about you.

554
00:26:45,060 --> 00:26:45,900
 "If you think it's about you,

555
00:26:45,900 --> 00:26:47,700
 "you're never gonna be happy."

556
00:26:47,700 --> 00:26:48,860
 If you think it's about another,

557
00:26:48,860 --> 00:26:52,740
 you have a chance of finding that happiness.

558
00:26:52,740 --> 00:26:56,380
 But we thought, who can we ask to come and speak to us

559
00:26:56,380 --> 00:26:59,940
 on service leadership?

560
00:26:59,940 --> 00:27:04,060
 And so, we immediately thought of Jackie Pullinger.

561
00:27:04,060 --> 00:27:06,380
 Now, what you may not know is that Jackie Pullinger

562
00:27:06,380 --> 00:27:10,060
 has an honorary doctorate from HKU.

563
00:27:10,060 --> 00:27:11,620
 So, that works really well.

564
00:27:11,620 --> 00:27:13,540
 But she also, and most importantly,

565
00:27:13,540 --> 00:27:18,140
 has dedicated her life and is continuing to serving others.

566
00:27:18,140 --> 00:27:19,900
 And so, we invited her to come on.

567
00:27:19,900 --> 00:27:21,300
 And so, we were interviewing her.

568
00:27:21,300 --> 00:27:22,140
 So, there's a stage,

569
00:27:22,140 --> 00:27:23,460
 and if you imagine you're all the students,

570
00:27:23,460 --> 00:27:24,940
 and then there's up here,

571
00:27:24,940 --> 00:27:28,100
 my co-leader was interviewing her, Francis Choi.

572
00:27:28,100 --> 00:27:31,220
 So, Francis Choi starts the interview by talking to Jackie,

573
00:27:31,220 --> 00:27:34,180
 and he says, "Jackie, you have done so much in your life,

574
00:27:34,180 --> 00:27:36,220
 "and you are doing so much in your life.

575
00:27:36,220 --> 00:27:39,780
 "You must be a very driven person."

576
00:27:39,780 --> 00:27:43,180
 And then, Jackie says this.

577
00:27:43,180 --> 00:27:46,300
 She says, "I'm not driven, I'm led."

578
00:27:46,300 --> 00:27:51,180
 Now, if you know Jackie, you know how she said that, right?

579
00:27:51,180 --> 00:27:54,820
 "I'm not driven, I'm led."

580
00:27:54,820 --> 00:27:59,820
 And that makes all the difference, if you think about it.

581
00:28:00,020 --> 00:28:03,020
 And for our students, it really struck home,

582
00:28:03,020 --> 00:28:04,920
 because they feel driven.

583
00:28:04,920 --> 00:28:07,900
 They feel driven to meet the expectations of others.

584
00:28:07,900 --> 00:28:09,780
 They feel driven to get the best job.

585
00:28:09,780 --> 00:28:11,180
 They feel driven.

586
00:28:11,180 --> 00:28:13,420
 It ran home to me.

587
00:28:13,420 --> 00:28:15,680
 I'm like taking notes in the back, right?

588
00:28:15,680 --> 00:28:17,840
 Because sometimes I feel driven.

589
00:28:17,840 --> 00:28:23,000
 And maybe it resonates with you.

590
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:26,860
 Maybe there's parts of you that feel more driven than led.

591
00:28:26,860 --> 00:28:29,860
 But in Jesus Christ, we are not driven.

592
00:28:29,860 --> 00:28:31,620
 We are led.

593
00:28:31,620 --> 00:28:32,460
 Amen?

594
00:28:32,460 --> 00:28:34,540
 Very simple.

595
00:28:34,540 --> 00:28:37,300
 Jesus, as a good leader, condensed it down

596
00:28:37,300 --> 00:28:39,620
 to two words of what we're supposed to do.

597
00:28:39,620 --> 00:28:42,060
 Follow me.

598
00:28:42,060 --> 00:28:44,080
 That's the plan.

599
00:28:44,080 --> 00:28:46,100
 That was the plan then.

600
00:28:46,100 --> 00:28:49,280
 That's the plan now, is that we follow him.

601
00:28:49,280 --> 00:28:53,300
 We are not driven by him.

602
00:28:53,300 --> 00:28:55,940
 We are led by him.

603
00:28:55,940 --> 00:29:00,940
 And Galatians 5.25 has this imagery of a dance, right?

604
00:29:00,940 --> 00:29:05,300
 And it's like stay in step with the Holy Spirit.

605
00:29:05,300 --> 00:29:09,100
 So the Holy Spirit's dancing, and we're staying in step.

606
00:29:09,100 --> 00:29:10,700
 Some years ago, Marian and I thought

607
00:29:10,700 --> 00:29:13,700
 we would do a couple dancing course.

608
00:29:13,700 --> 00:29:14,580
 And it was fun.

609
00:29:14,580 --> 00:29:17,180
 We had a fun time doing it.

610
00:29:17,180 --> 00:29:20,220
 But we had a problem, because it was couples dancing,

611
00:29:20,220 --> 00:29:21,860
 so someone has to lead, right?

612
00:29:21,860 --> 00:29:23,300
 And we're both leaders.

613
00:29:23,300 --> 00:29:24,840
 So this was a trouble, right?

614
00:29:24,840 --> 00:29:26,100
 No one wanted to follow.

615
00:29:26,100 --> 00:29:32,140
 But it's not a question in the Holy Spirit.

616
00:29:32,140 --> 00:29:34,700
 We follow the Holy Spirit.

617
00:29:34,700 --> 00:29:39,140
 And trust me, he has a better plan than I do or you do.

618
00:29:39,140 --> 00:29:40,700
 So we follow the Holy Spirit.

619
00:29:40,700 --> 00:29:42,460
 Now, think about those two things,

620
00:29:42,460 --> 00:29:43,940
 following the Holy Spirit.

621
00:29:43,940 --> 00:29:45,660
 Think about we're not driven, we're not led.

622
00:29:45,660 --> 00:29:48,340
 And then let's read through the rest of this passage

623
00:29:48,340 --> 00:29:49,500
 as we get into it.

624
00:29:49,500 --> 00:29:53,460
 So we begin again, and we pick up with verse 27.

625
00:29:53,460 --> 00:29:56,020
 "When the jailer woke and he saw

626
00:29:56,020 --> 00:29:57,560
 "that the prison doors were open,

627
00:29:57,560 --> 00:30:00,700
 "he drew his sword and was about to kill himself,

628
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:03,620
 "supposing that the prisoners had escaped.

629
00:30:03,620 --> 00:30:06,060
 "But Paul cried out with a loud voice,

630
00:30:06,060 --> 00:30:08,780
 "'Do not harm yourself, for we are all here.'

631
00:30:08,780 --> 00:30:11,020
 "And the jailer called for lights and rushed in,

632
00:30:11,020 --> 00:30:13,860
 "and trembling with fear, the jailer fell down

633
00:30:13,860 --> 00:30:15,580
 "before Paul and Silas."

634
00:30:15,580 --> 00:30:16,980
 This is a turn of events.

635
00:30:16,980 --> 00:30:19,180
 "And then he brought them out and said,

636
00:30:19,180 --> 00:30:21,900
 "'Sirs, what must I do to be saved?'"

637
00:30:21,900 --> 00:30:24,820
 And that word there, saved, literally means,

638
00:30:24,820 --> 00:30:28,740
 it means rescued, it means wholeness,

639
00:30:28,740 --> 00:30:32,000
 complete healing, well-being, it means life overflowing,

640
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:33,740
 as Carla was talking earlier.

641
00:30:33,740 --> 00:30:36,200
 "What must I do to be saved?

642
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:37,780
 "And they said, 'Believe,'"

643
00:30:37,780 --> 00:30:39,600
 and that word is literally trust,

644
00:30:39,600 --> 00:30:41,400
 "in the Lord Jesus, and you will be saved,

645
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:42,320
 "you and your household.'

646
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:44,500
 "And they spoke the word of the Lord to him."

647
00:30:44,500 --> 00:30:46,640
 Do you see how this and is working?

648
00:30:46,640 --> 00:30:48,460
 It doesn't say Paul or Timothy,

649
00:30:48,460 --> 00:30:49,660
 they're just working together.

650
00:30:49,660 --> 00:30:51,380
 They spoke the word of the Lord to him.

651
00:30:51,380 --> 00:30:53,020
 "And he took them the same hour of the night,

652
00:30:53,020 --> 00:30:56,740
 "and he washed their wounds, and he was baptized."

653
00:30:56,740 --> 00:30:59,780
 So now we're seeing a conversion experience

654
00:30:59,780 --> 00:31:01,700
 of the jailer, right?

655
00:31:01,700 --> 00:31:05,660
 He's making reparations, he's making right for his wrongs,

656
00:31:05,660 --> 00:31:08,380
 he's washing them, there's the water of baptism,

657
00:31:08,380 --> 00:31:10,880
 then it goes on, and he invites them into their home,

658
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:14,580
 there's hospitality, he sets food on the table for them,

659
00:31:14,580 --> 00:31:16,780
 right, this is where we like it as Hong Kongers, right?

660
00:31:16,780 --> 00:31:19,120
 There's food now, and of course, when food comes,

661
00:31:19,120 --> 00:31:20,660
 then also joy comes, right?

662
00:31:20,660 --> 00:31:24,740
 And then it says after that, then there's joy, joy,

663
00:31:24,740 --> 00:31:29,020
 unbelievable joy, and I don't think we talk enough

664
00:31:29,020 --> 00:31:33,580
 about joy and salvation together, but there's joy.

665
00:31:33,580 --> 00:31:45,940
 When I came to the Lord in Northern Nigeria,

666
00:31:46,980 --> 00:31:51,300
 it just was an experience that I knew this is right,

667
00:31:51,300 --> 00:31:52,400
 and there was joy.

668
00:31:52,400 --> 00:31:56,140
 So let me say this, if there's anyone here

669
00:31:56,140 --> 00:31:59,300
 who has not yet said, "I wanna follow him,"

670
00:31:59,300 --> 00:32:03,140
 like we've just heard, why not now?

671
00:32:03,140 --> 00:32:05,940
 Why not even today if the Lord is speaking to you?

672
00:32:05,940 --> 00:32:08,820
 Because there's always this invitation, follow me.

673
00:32:08,820 --> 00:32:11,100
 And all we have to do is kinda crack the window

674
00:32:11,100 --> 00:32:14,580
 a little bit of our hearts, and this joy and change

675
00:32:14,580 --> 00:32:18,660
 and rightness comes sweeping in, but we do have to act.

676
00:32:18,660 --> 00:32:20,900
 We do have to say yes, 'cause he's not someone

677
00:32:20,900 --> 00:32:23,580
 who's gonna force himself on anyone.

678
00:32:23,580 --> 00:32:26,340
 And so we say yes.

679
00:32:26,340 --> 00:32:28,580
 It's the easiest thing in the world to do,

680
00:32:28,580 --> 00:32:33,400
 'cause all you have to do is give everything to Jesus.

681
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:37,060
 It's the hardest thing in the world to do,

682
00:32:37,060 --> 00:32:40,640
 'cause all you have to do is give everything to Jesus.

683
00:32:40,640 --> 00:32:43,980
 But trust me, it's worth it.

684
00:32:44,980 --> 00:32:49,420
 And if you're online, also you're invited.

685
00:32:49,420 --> 00:32:56,260
 But most of us in this room probably have said yes,

686
00:32:56,260 --> 00:32:57,340
 and we've been following.

687
00:32:57,340 --> 00:32:58,660
 Sometimes it's been in the dark,

688
00:32:58,660 --> 00:33:00,540
 sometimes we're not sure exactly where it's going.

689
00:33:00,540 --> 00:33:02,500
 Jesus is going, but we follow him.

690
00:33:02,500 --> 00:33:06,980
 And so the dance for us is not the dance of salvation.

691
00:33:06,980 --> 00:33:11,540
 The dance for us is the dance of staying in step

692
00:33:11,540 --> 00:33:12,880
 on a daily basis.

693
00:33:12,880 --> 00:33:15,060
 Now, if the dance metaphor is not working for you,

694
00:33:15,060 --> 00:33:16,660
 that's fine, we can choose another one.

695
00:33:16,660 --> 00:33:20,300
 You can say like music with, maybe it's a orchestra

696
00:33:20,300 --> 00:33:22,260
 and the leader is guiding everybody

